headline: 2 Software Stocks Worth Your Attention and 1 to Think Twice About
summary: Software is rapidly reducing operating expenses for businesses. This secular theme makes SaaS companies attractive investment candidates but also comes with higher valuations that cause volatility. Unfortunately, the rich prices have haunted them over the past six months as the industry has shed 11%. This drop was worse than the S&P 500’s 3.6% loss.
